The Nasrul-Lahi-il Fathi Society of Nigeria (NASFAT) has held the 2nd edition of its National Education Summit in Osogbo, Osun State capital. The President of (NASFAF), Yusuf Olaniyi, charged Muslims to take education as part of religion and ensure that their children are well educated. The summit was organised by NASFAT in collaboration with Fountain University, Osogbo. Yusuf said the four cardinal objectives of NASFAT are education, health, livelihood and propagation of Islam, Dawah.